1. SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS (MUST HAVE)
Ask the other person to install these first:
‚úÖ Install Node.js
Download from: https://nodejs.org
Install LTS version
Verify installation:
node -v
npm -v
‚úÖ Install Git (optional, but recommended)
Download from: https://git-scm.com
2. PROJECT STRUCTURE (IMPORTANT)
After downloading/cloning, the folder structure must look like this:
projects/
 bsp dashboard/    ‚Üê FRONTEND (React)
src/
package.json
vite.config.js
bsp-backend/      ‚Üê BACKEND (Node.js)
server.js
package.json

3. BACKEND SETUP & RUN (FIRST)
üîπ Step 3.1: Open backend folder
cd bsp-backend
You should see:
server.js
package.json

Step 3.3: Run backend server
node server.js
‚úÖ Expected output:
Backend running on http://localhost:8080

FRONTEND SETUP & RUN (SECOND)
üîπ Step 4.1: Open frontend folder (new terminal)
cd "bsp dashboard"
Step 4.2: Install frontend dependencies
npm install
üîπ Step 4.3: Install charts library (required)
npm install recharts

Step 4.4: Check API configuration
Open file:
src/services/api.js

It MUST be:
import axios from "axios";
export const api = axios.create({
  baseURL: "http://localhost:8080"
});

Step 4.5: Run frontend
npm run dev

STOPPING THE PROJECT

To stop:
Press Ctrl + C in backend terminal
Press Ctrl + C in frontend terminal
